<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="D" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Downy" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Downy,</orth> 1) covered or furnished with down or soft hair: <cit><quote>a d. feather,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.5.32" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 5, 32</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>d. cygnets,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 5.3.56" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A V, 3, 56</bibl></cit>. <emph>d. windows</emph> (viz the eyelids) <bibl n="shak. ant 5.2.319" default="NO" valid="yes">Ant. V, 2, 319</bibl>.<lb />2) soft, placid: <cit><quote>shake off this d. sleep,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 2.3.81" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. II, 3, 81</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>